        <num>10-6-3</num>
        <content>
          <p>Any person who is of sound mind may be appointed an agent; so a principal shall be bound by the acts of his infant agent.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2159; Code 1868, § 2155; Code 1873, § 2181; Code 1882, § 2181; Civil Code 1895, § 3001; Civil Code 1910, § 3573; Code 1933, § 4-102.)</p>
